Former Governor Mario Cuomo's passing has saddened Vice President Joe Biden and his wife, Jill. They express their admiration for Cuomo, describing him as one of the most principled and courageous public servants they have known. Cuomo was a strong advocate for civil rights, equal rights, economic opportunity, and justice. He was willing to stand by his convictions, even when they were unpopular. Despite the challenges, Cuomo remained hopeful and optimistic about the future of the country and its people. The Vice President extends his condolences to the entire Cuomo family, acknowledging Cuomo as a good man.